            . I know Mr. George Harrison - he is a <rs id="t18280703-162-viclabel810" type="occupation">carpenter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280703-162-victim943 t18280703-162-viclabel810"></join>, and lives at Pimlico. This wood was taken from the <placeName id="t18280703-162-crimeloc811">Shot and Shell wharf at Blackwall</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280703-162-crimeloc811" type="placeName" value="Shot and Shell wharf at Blackwall"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280703-162-crimeloc811" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280703-162-off808 t18280703-162-crimeloc811"></join> - it is shut up at night: I missed three pieces of wood, and on the 3d of June I found one of them on the Anchor wharf - I know it to be Mr. Harrison's; the prisoner was sawing it up - he said he did not know whose it was; I said "You knew it was not yours" - he was at work there, digging post-holes for anchors.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280703-162-person945">
                  JOHN 
                  WEBB
               <interp inst="t18280703-162-person945" type="surname" value="WEBB"></interp>
